{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01QxrA3xJSbnshGa1Pt2TJYu","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Excellent! Now I have a comprehensive picture. Let me summarize the findings:\n\n## Title Extraction Iteration History and Feedback Summary\n\n### Overview of Iterations\n\nThe title extraction loop has run **29 iterations** with improvements tracked from iteration 25 onwards. The performance trajectory shows:\n- **Iteration 25:** 100% accuracy (11/11 real files), 1 generated failure → 99.5% combined\n- **Iteration 26:** 85.6% combined accuracy (16 generated failures, 0 real)\n- **Iteration 27:** 90.1% combined accuracy (11 generated failures, 0 real)\n- **Iteration 28:** 90.1% combined accuracy (11 generated failures, 0 real) — fixes stalled\n- **Iteration 29:** 91.9% combined accuracy (9 generated failures, 0 real) — modest improvement\n\n**Key insight:** Real files have maintained 100% accuracy since iteration 25. All failures are on generated test files, suggesting the core algorithm works well but has edge-case handling gaps.\n\n---\n\n### Failure Pattern Evolution\n\n#### Iteration 25 (Baseline)\n- Single real-file failure: OCR artifact `DAT FLATBREADS` misidentified as part of compound title\n- Root cause: Orphaned all-caps strings without corroborating context\n\n#### Iteration 26-28 (Recurring patterns across 3 iterations)\n\n**Pattern A: OCR Digit-for-Letter Corruption** (5 cases across 26-28)\n- Examples: `Bra1sed Cod w1th Wh1te W1ne`, `Roasted Beet and Walnut D1p`\n- Behaviors: Returns empty OR wrong body line\n- Root cause: The blind OCR repair was mapping `1→l` instead of `1→i` for mixed-case text\n- Impact: Fixed in iteration 28's code review (see Fix A below)\n\n**Pattern B: Section Headers / Metadata Before Title** (3 cases, consistent across iterations)\n- Examples: `FISH & SEAFOOD` before title; pipe-separated metadata `Lato | Zupy | ...` before title\n- Extractor behavior: Picks wrong line or returns empty\n- Root cause: Direct-successor bonus checks `lines[position - 1]` but misses blank lines between header and title\n- Impact: Partially addressed; needs blank-line-aware scanning\n\n**Pattern C: Corrupted Title → Wrong Body Line** (3 cases)\n- Examples: `Drożdże Sern1k → \"Podaw4ć letni lub chłodny.\"` (serving instruction)\n- Root cause: Corrupted title rejected, then body line outscores fallback candidates\n- Fix direction: Prefer first non-empty line positionally over best-scored line\n\n**Pattern D: Multi-line Split Title** (1 case, then resolved)\n- Example: `LEMON HERB RO45TED` / `VEGETABLES` on separate lines\n- Fixed by detecting short title + short all-caps follow-up line and merging\n\n**Pattern E: Title Absent from Document Start** (2-5 cases)\n- Examples: Pages starting mid-recipe with spillover marker, or Mushroom Risotto picking wrong recipe title\n- Behaviors: Returns empty OR picks next recipe's title OR picks instruction line\n- Root cause: Overflow marker regex didn't match actual test markers; prologue detection didn't handle interleaved instruction/prose\n\n---\n\n### Iteration 28 Code Review & Fixes Applied\n\nThe iteration 28 review identified **4 bugs that were directly fixed:**\n\n1. **Fix A: Blind OCR repair defaulted to `l` instead of `i`**\n   - File: `title-extractor.ts:881`\n   - Changed `applyBlindOcrRepairToken(token, \"l\")` → `applyBlindOcrRepairToken(token, \"i\")`\n   - Impact: HIGH — prevents re-corruption of correctly-scored titles\n\n2. **Fix B: ALL_CAPS branch regex incomplete**\n   - File: `title-extractor.ts:849-850`\n   - Widened `[A-Z]` → `[A-ZÀ-Ż]` for Polish characters\n   - Impact: MEDIUM — handles Polish titles like `ŻUREK`\n\n3. **Fix C: `isProse` dead code, unified prologue detector inconsistent**\n   - File: `title-extractor.ts:487-495`\n   - Replaced with two clearly separated predicates: `isContinuation` (2+ words) vs `isBodyEnding` (4+ words)\n   - Impact: MEDIUM — clarifies interleaved instruction/prose detection\n\n4. **Fix D: `burstEnd` fallback inverted**\n   - File: `title-extractor.ts:727, 730`\n   - Changed `?? 0` → `?? lines.length`\n   - Impact: LOW — edge case but semantically incorrect\n\n---\n\n### Iteration 29 Improvement Plan (Current)\n\nThe plan identifies 7 remaining failure patterns:\n\n1. **OCR digit-for-letter in title → empty extraction** (2 cases)\n   - Root cause: Corrupted first line rejected, no fallback\n   - Fix: Improve digit-to-letter normalization before scoring\n\n2. **OCR digit-for-letter in title → wrong body line extracted** (2 cases)\n   - Root cause: Body line wins scoring over corrupted title\n   - Fix: Strong positional prior for first non-metadata line\n\n3. **OCR garbage tokens → wrong body line extracted** (1 case)\n   - Example: `Żurek Krakowski → \"Xxyyzz salt and pepper\"`\n   - Root cause: Garbage tokens outscore clean title\n\n4. **Mixed-case + special chars in title → wrong body line** (1 case)\n   - Example: `KoPyTka z P¡eczarkami Leśnymi → \"Ugotuj ziemniaky. (38)\"`\n   - Root cause: Erratic casing makes title unrecognizable\n\n5. **Metadata header before title → empty extraction** (1 case)\n   - Example: `Ogórkowa Zupa` with pipe-separated metadata header\n   - Root cause: Metadata region processing confuses position logic\n\n6. **Title absent from document → wrong title extracted** (1 case)\n   - Example: `Mushroom Risotto` document starts mid-recipe, picks `CARPACCIO DI PESCE SPADA`\n   - Root cause: Structural scan problem (unfixable without semantic understanding)\n\n7. **Partial OCR normalization → near-miss extraction** (1 case)\n   - Example: `S01e with Brown Butter and Capers` (missing `0→o` fix)\n   - Root cause: Incomplete digit-to-letter correction map\n\n**Proposed fixes in iteration 29 plan:**\n- Fix 1: Dual-variant blind OCR repair (generate both `1→i` and `1→l` variants, let embedding scorer choose)\n- Fix 1B: Normalize erratic casing before OCR repair\n- Fix 2: Blank-line-aware direct-successor bonus\n- Fix 3: Improved overflow marker regex matching\n- Fix 4: Non-consecutive instruction prologue detection\n\n---\n\n### Current Status (as of March 17, 2026)\n\n- **Branch:** `feat/title_extraction_loop`\n- **Recent commits:** 28-29 iterations with incremental improvements\n- **Test results:** 91.9% combined (generated + real), with 0 real-file failures\n- **Outstanding issues:** 9 generated-file failures remain, primarily edge cases involving OCR corruption patterns and document structure detection\n- **Code quality:** Clean architecture; identified performance optimization opportunities (caching, deduplication) not yet implemented\n\nThis represents a mature, well-tested system with high real-world accuracy but with remaining challenges in handling pathological OCR corruption and unusual document structures."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: adb42d6d60a612000 (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 100865\ntool_uses: 14\nduration_ms: 75780</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c37a3300-1904-44e6-bf34-65ba8b38fada","uuid":"6978ff46-04ca-4313-84f3-67ac1d4b2488","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"I need to understand the title extraction iteration history and current feedback. Please:\n\n1. Read tools/title-loop/docs/29-e7e3098/feedback.md\n2. Read tools/title-loop/docs/28-1ac016c/ - any files there\n3. Read tools/title-loop/docs/iter.txt\n4. List all directories in tools/title-loop/docs/ to understand the iteration history\n5. Read the most recent 3-4 iteration feedback files to understand the trajectory of changes\n\nBe thorough - read everything available in the iteration 29 directory, and sample recent iterations (27, 28) to understand what's been tried.","agentId":"adb42d6d60a612000","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Excellent! Now I have a comprehensive picture. Let me summarize the findings:\n\n## Title Extraction Iteration History and Feedback Summary\n\n### Overview of Iterations\n\nThe title extraction loop has run **29 iterations** with improvements tracked from iteration 25 onwards. The performance trajectory shows:\n- **Iteration 25:** 100% accuracy (11/11 real files), 1 generated failure → 99.5% combined\n- **Iteration 26:** 85.6% combined accuracy (16 generated failures, 0 real)\n- **Iteration 27:** 90.1% combined accuracy (11 generated failures, 0 real)\n- **Iteration 28:** 90.1% combined accuracy (11 generated failures, 0 real) — fixes stalled\n- **Iteration 29:** 91.9% combined accuracy (9 generated failures, 0 real) — modest improvement\n\n**Key insight:** Real files have maintained 100% accuracy since iteration 25. All failures are on generated test files, suggesting the core algorithm works well but has edge-case handling gaps.\n\n---\n\n### Failure Pattern Evolution\n\n#### Iteration 25 (Baseline)\n- Single real-file failure: OCR artifact `DAT FLATBREADS` misidentified as part of compound title\n- Root cause: Orphaned all-caps strings without corroborating context\n\n#### Iteration 26-28 (Recurring patterns across 3 iterations)\n\n**Pattern A: OCR Digit-for-Letter Corruption** (5 cases across 26-28)\n- Examples: `Bra1sed Cod w1th Wh1te W1ne`, `Roasted Beet and Walnut D1p`\n- Behaviors: Returns empty OR wrong body line\n- Root cause: The blind OCR repair was mapping `1→l` instead of `1→i` for mixed-case text\n- Impact: Fixed in iteration 28's code review (see Fix A below)\n\n**Pattern B: Section Headers / Metadata Before Title** (3 cases, consistent across iterations)\n- Examples: `FISH & SEAFOOD` before title; pipe-separated metadata `Lato | Zupy | ...` before title\n- Extractor behavior: Picks wrong line or returns empty\n- Root cause: Direct-successor bonus checks `lines[position - 1]` but misses blank lines between header and title\n- Impact: Partially addressed; needs blank-line-aware scanning\n\n**Pattern C: Corrupted Title → Wrong Body Line** (3 cases)\n- Examples: `Drożdże Sern1k → \"Podaw4ć letni lub chłodny.\"` (serving instruction)\n- Root cause: Corrupted title rejected, then body line outscores fallback candidates\n- Fix direction: Prefer first non-empty line positionally over best-scored line\n\n**Pattern D: Multi-line Split Title** (1 case, then resolved)\n- Example: `LEMON HERB RO45TED` / `VEGETABLES` on separate lines\n- Fixed by detecting short title + short all-caps follow-up line and merging\n\n**Pattern E: Title Absent from Document Start** (2-5 cases)\n- Examples: Pages starting mid-recipe with spillover marker, or Mushroom Risotto picking wrong recipe title\n- Behaviors: Returns empty OR picks next recipe's title OR picks instruction line\n- Root cause: Overflow marker regex didn't match actual test markers; prologue detection didn't handle interleaved instruction/prose\n\n---\n\n### Iteration 28 Code Review & Fixes Applied\n\nThe iteration 28 review identified **4 bugs that were directly fixed:**\n\n1. **Fix A: Blind OCR repair defaulted to `l` instead of `i`**\n   - File: `title-extractor.ts:881`\n   - Changed `applyBlindOcrRepairToken(token, \"l\")` → `applyBlindOcrRepairToken(token, \"i\")`\n   - Impact: HIGH — prevents re-corruption of correctly-scored titles\n\n2. **Fix B: ALL_CAPS branch regex incomplete**\n   - File: `title-extractor.ts:849-850`\n   - Widened `[A-Z]` → `[A-ZÀ-Ż]` for Polish characters\n   - Impact: MEDIUM — handles Polish titles like `ŻUREK`\n\n3. **Fix C: `isProse` dead code, unified prologue detector inconsistent**\n   - File: `title-extractor.ts:487-495`\n   - Replaced with two clearly separated predicates: `isContinuation` (2+ words) vs `isBodyEnding` (4+ words)\n   - Impact: MEDIUM — clarifies interleaved instruction/prose detection\n\n4. **Fix D: `burstEnd` fallback inverted**\n   - File: `title-extractor.ts:727, 730`\n   - Changed `?? 0` → `?? lines.length`\n   - Impact: LOW — edge case but semantically incorrect\n\n---\n\n### Iteration 29 Improvement Plan (Current)\n\nThe plan identifies 7 remaining failure patterns:\n\n1. **OCR digit-for-letter in title → empty extraction** (2 cases)\n   - Root cause: Corrupted first line rejected, no fallback\n   - Fix: Improve digit-to-letter normalization before scoring\n\n2. **OCR digit-for-letter in title → wrong body line extracted** (2 cases)\n   - Root cause: Body line wins scoring over corrupted title\n   - Fix: Strong positional prior for first non-metadata line\n\n3. **OCR garbage tokens → wrong body line extracted** (1 case)\n   - Example: `Żurek Krakowski → \"Xxyyzz salt and pepper\"`\n   - Root cause: Garbage tokens outscore clean title\n\n4. **Mixed-case + special chars in title → wrong body line** (1 case)\n   - Example: `KoPyTka z P¡eczarkami Leśnymi → \"Ugotuj ziemniaky. (38)\"`\n   - Root cause: Erratic casing makes title unrecognizable\n\n5. **Metadata header before title → empty extraction** (1 case)\n   - Example: `Ogórkowa Zupa` with pipe-separated metadata header\n   - Root cause: Metadata region processing confuses position logic\n\n6. **Title absent from document → wrong title extracted** (1 case)\n   - Example: `Mushroom Risotto` document starts mid-recipe, picks `CARPACCIO DI PESCE SPADA`\n   - Root cause: Structural scan problem (unfixable without semantic understanding)\n\n7. **Partial OCR normalization → near-miss extraction** (1 case)\n   - Example: `S01e with Brown Butter and Capers` (missing `0→o` fix)\n   - Root cause: Incomplete digit-to-letter correction map\n\n**Proposed fixes in iteration 29 plan:**\n- Fix 1: Dual-variant blind OCR repair (generate both `1→i` and `1→l` variants, let embedding scorer choose)\n- Fix 1B: Normalize erratic casing before OCR repair\n- Fix 2: Blank-line-aware direct-successor bonus\n- Fix 3: Improved overflow marker regex matching\n- Fix 4: Non-consecutive instruction prologue detection\n\n---\n\n### Current Status (as of March 17, 2026)\n\n- **Branch:** `feat/title_extraction_loop`\n- **Recent commits:** 28-29 iterations with incremental improvements\n- **Test results:** 91.9% combined (generated + real), with 0 real-file failures\n- **Outstanding issues:** 9 generated-file failures remain, primarily edge cases involving OCR corruption patterns and document structure detection\n- **Code quality:** Clean architecture; identified performance optimization opportunities (caching, deduplication) not yet implemented\n\nThis represents a mature, well-tested system with high real-world accuracy but with remaining challenges in handling pathological OCR corruption and unusual document structures."}],"totalDurationMs":75780,"totalTokens":100865,"totalToolUseCount":14,"usage":{"input_tokens":5,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1246,"cache_read_input_tokens":97728,"output_tokens":1886,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1246},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
