{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_014b1jaBC4e9WcCkenNgu7VB","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Excellent! Now I have a comprehensive understanding of the system. Let me create a detailed summary:\n\n## Complete Title Extraction Implementation Analysis\n\nI've conducted a thorough analysis of the title extraction implementation. Here's the complete pipeline:\n\n---\n\n### **1. MAIN ENTRY POINT**\n**File:** `/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/lib/text-classifier/title-extractor.ts` (1,665 lines)\n\n**Two modes:**\n- `extractTitle()` - Fast synchronous heuristic fallback (finds first non-filtered line)\n- `extractTitleWithEmbeddings()` - Full semantic pipeline with MiniLM embeddings\n\n---\n\n### **2. CANDIDATE GENERATION PIPELINE**\n\n#### **2.1 Build Candidates (`buildCandidates` function, lines 537-731)**\n\n**Input:** Array of text lines\n\n**Steps:**\n\n1. **Collect non-empty lines** with original indices\n2. **Find burst end** - Skip initial preamble of garbled/short lines\n3. **Pre-join hyphen-broken lines** - \"ROASTED CHICKEN-\" + \"ABLES\" → single line\n4. **Pre-merge ALL_CAPS sequences** - Group consecutive short ALL_CAPS fragments into one candidate\n5. **Pre-merge continuation lines** - Lines starting with `/&+:(` get merged with preceding line\n6. **Build candidate pool**:\n   - Single-line candidates (after OCR repair)\n   - Blind OCR variants for early-position candidates (with digit→letter substitution)\n   - 2-line joins\n   - 3-line joins\n   - Deduplication via lowercase normalization\n\n7. **Pre-filter to 25 candidates** - Keep ALL_CAPS and short ones first\n\n**Output:** Up to 25 candidates with `{ text, position, origin }`\n\n#### **2.2 Hard Filters (`passesHardFilters`, lines 385-426)**\n\nCandidate must NOT be:\n- Outside 3-80 character range\n- Ingredient line (measurement units, quantities)\n- Starting with a number or fraction\n- Recipe metadata (serving sizes, prep times, Polish/English patterns)\n- Garbled (low/high vowel ratio, internal caps, isolated short words)\n- Cooking instruction (English/Polish verb starts)\n- Pipe-separated or trailing page numbers\n- Multiple slashes (navigation breadcrumbs)\n- Bullet points\n- Section labels (INGREDIENTS, SKŁADNIKI, etc.)\n- 8+ words without separators (body text)\n- Known non-title words (single words: \"the\", \"and\", etc.)\n\n---\n\n### **3. SCORING SYSTEM**\n\n#### **3.1 Reference Embeddings (Semantic Anchors)**\n\nThree reference phrases:\n```\nTITLE_REFERENCE = \"recipe name, dish title, name of the food, nazwa przepisu, nazwa dania\"\nHEADER_REFERENCE = \"ingredients list, cooking directions, section heading, składniki, przygotowanie, sposób wykonania\"\nNOISE_REFERENCE = \"page number, table of contents, book footer, garbled text\"\n```\n\n#### **3.2 Raw Score Calculation (Pass 1, lines 1025-1034)**\n\nFor each candidate:\n```\nembedding = embed(candidate_text)\ntitleSim = cosineSimilarity(embedding, titleRefEmbedding)\nheaderSim = cosineSimilarity(embedding, headerRefEmbedding)\nnoiseSim = cosineSimilarity(embedding, noiseRefEmbedding)\nrawScore = titleSim - Math.max(headerSim, noiseSim)\n```\n\n**Logic:** Maximize title similarity while penalizing header/noise resemblance.\n\n#### **3.3 Structural Heading Detection (lines 1019-1086)**\n\nSelect best ALL_CAPS candidate (≥2 words, ≥4 alpha chars per word):\n- Ranked by `rawScore`\n- Check for truncation artifacts (e.g., \"FRON\" vs \"SAFFRON\")\n- Find continuation joins (with `/&+:(` prefix on next line)\n\n#### **3.4 Bonus System (Pass 2, lines 1089-1189)**\n\nApplied to all candidates:\n\n| Bonus | Trigger | Amount | Notes |\n|-------|---------|--------|-------|\n| **ALL_CAPS bonus** | ALL_CAPS text with ≥4 letters | +0.08 (multi-word) or +0.03 (single-word) | Single words get reduced bonus (likely section labels) |\n| **Structural bonus** | Best ALL_CAPS heading or its continuation | +0.10 | Applied to `firstStructuralHeading` |\n| **Position factor** | Candidate rank in pool | 1.0 to 1.24x multiplier | Earlier candidates get 1.0-1.24x boost; dampens after 50% |\n| **Preamble bonus** | First candidate after filtered/empty lines | +0.08 or +0.12 | Higher if preamble had structural markers |\n| **Direct-successor bonus** | Top 3 candidates following section label/metadata | +0.10 | Fires independently of first-after-preamble |\n\n**Capped positional boost:** All positional bonuses combined ≤ +0.15\n\n**Three score variants:**\n- `rawScore` - Pure embedding signal (≥-0.05 for early pos, ≥0.02 for later)\n- `baseScore` - rawScore + allCapsBonus + structuralBonus (diagnostics)\n- `thresholdScore` - rawScore + allCapsBonus (excludes structural, prevents inflation on multi-recipe pages)\n- `score` - rawScore × positionFactor + allCapsBonus + structuralBonus (final ranking)\n\n---\n\n### **4. MULTI-TITLE & BILINGUAL DETECTION**\n\n#### **4.1 Bilingual Title Suppression (lines 1191-1276)**\n\n**Pattern 1: Mixed-case + ALL_CAPS pair**\n- Detect if position-0 mixed-case candidate is followed by ALL_CAPS at position ≤2\n- Check embedding similarity (>0.4 cosine) or word-overlap non-matching\n- Suppress translation candidates from threshold calculation\n\n**Pattern 2: ALL_CAPS translation reassignment**\n- If structural heading is identified as translation, reassign it to non-translation alternative\n\n**Pattern 3: Subtitle suppression**\n- Short mixed-case at position 0 + longer mixed-case at position 1-2 with >2 extra words\n- Apply -0.15 penalty to longer one\n\n**Pattern 4: Mixed-case + mixed-case bilingual layout**\n- Position 0: ≤2 words\n- Position 1-2: 2-5 words, mixed-case, not ingredient/instruction\n- Section label nearby (within 6 lines)\n- Boost position-0 candidate by +0.15\n\n#### **4.2 Threshold Calculation (lines 1359-1362)**\n\n```\nbestThresholdScore = max(scoredForThreshold[*].thresholdScore)\nthreshold = max(0.08, bestThresholdScore × 0.7)\n```\n\n**Selects:** Candidates with `score >= threshold`\n\n#### **4.3 Fallback Logic (lines 1367-1381)**\n\nIf threshold filters all candidates:\n- Use best positional candidate\n- Relax `rawScore` requirement for position ≤2 (≥-0.05) vs position >2 (≥0.02)\n\n#### **4.4 Title-Absent Page Guard (lines 1383-1391)**\n\nWhen first 3 non-empty lines are all ingredients/instructions/prose:\n- Require `rawScore >= 0.10` (strict)\n- Discard candidates beyond position 2\n\n---\n\n### **5. DEDUPLICATION & MULTI-TITLE LOGIC**\n\n#### **5.1 Pre-dedup Filters**\n\n1. **Structural heading prefix removal** (lines 1393-1408)\n   - Remove space-delimited prefixes of `firstStructuralHeading` if heading itself passed threshold\n\n2. **Continuation join protection** (lines 1410-1442)\n   - Protect 2-line/3-line joins from being removed by their single-line prefix/suffix\n\n3. **Sub-section header removal** (lines 1444-1465)\n   - Remove ALL_CAPS followed by ingredients if longer candidate contains it\n\n4. **Multi-line join component protection** (lines 1467-1485)\n   - If \"Lamb Stew\" (join) survives AND both \"Lamb\" + \"Stew\" (singles) survive, remove singles\n\n5. **Position-0 compound protection** (lines 1487-1503)\n   - Remove shorter candidates >10 lines away from position-0 compound if contained in it\n\n#### **5.2 Core Dedup Rule (lines 1505-1534)**\n\n**\"Shorter wins\":** If candidate A is a substring of candidate B, remove A\n- EXCEPTION: Compound titles with `[+:&]` separators protected\n- EXCEPTION: Multi-line join with food-category label suffix protected (e.g., \"LEMON HERB ROASTED VEGETABLES\")\n\n#### **5.3 Multi-Title Selection (lines 1536-1618)**\n\n**For ≥2 survivors:**\n\n- **≥2 ALL_CAPS:** Multi-recipe page. Use corroborated candidates (vocabulary support in document). Check if non-first headings are sub-headers (followed by ingredients) → if so, keep only first.\n- **1 ALL_CAPS:** Check relative position. If in last 25% of document, prefer earlier candidates (likely category footer).\n- **0 ALL_CAPS:** Mixed-case page. If span >10 lines, apply positional tiebreak (keep earliest high-scorer). If ≤10 lines span, keep all (genuine multi-recipe).\n\n**Final:** Cap at 3, join with \" + \"\n\n---\n\n### **6. OCR REPAIR**\n\n#### **6.1 Dictionary-Guided Repair (`repairOcrWord`, lines 773-801)**\n\n**Substitution map:**\n```\n\"0\" → \"o\", \"1\" → [\"i\", \"l\"], \"4\" → \"a\", \"5\" → \"s\"\n\"¡\" → \"i\", \"í\" → [\"i\", \"l\"], \"€\" → \"e\"\n```\n\n**Process:** Generate all combinations and check against FOOD_DICTIONARY (Polish + English ingredients, cooking terms, adjectives)\n\n#### **6.2 Blind OCR Repair (`applyBlindOcrRepair`, lines 875-890)**\n\nUsed for early-position candidates with artifacts:\n- ALL_CAPS: 1→I, 0→O, 4→A, 5→S\n- Mixed-case: 1→i (default) or 1→l (fallback), plus special cases for ¡/€\n\n#### **6.3 Erratic Casing Normalization (lines 892-912)**\n\nDetect words with ≥2 internal caps and ≥30% lowercase → capitalize first, lowercase rest\n\n#### **6.4 Post-Processing (`normalizeOcrTitle`, lines 946-976)**\n\n1. Dictionary repair\n2. Strip trailing section markers (+ SERVING AND STORAGE:, etc.)\n3. Blind OCR character substitution\n4. Title-case conversion (only if substitution changed the text)\n5. Normalize erratic casing\n\n---\n\n### **7. HELPER FILTERS & DETECTORS**\n\n| Function | Purpose |\n|----------|---------|\n| `looksLikeIngredient()` | Detect measurement units or \"to taste\" |\n| `startsWithNumber()` | Detect numbered lists |\n| `isAllCaps()` | Case detection |\n| `looksLikeMetadata()` | SERVES, PREP TIME, DLA, GODZ, etc. |\n| `isLikelyGarbled()` | Vowel ratio, pipes, Cyrillic, caps transitions, etc. |\n| `looksLikeCookingInstruction()` | English/Polish verb starts (beat, fold, smaż, etc.) |\n| `isSectionLabel()` | INGREDIENTS, SKŁADNIKI, WARZYWA, etc. |\n| `isBodyProse()` | Lowercase-start + 4+ words |\n| `isTitleAbsentPage()` | First 3 lines all ingredients/instructions |\n| `passesCorroboration()` | Vocabulary support check (≥67% or 100% for ≤3 words) |\n| `findBurstEnd()` | Skip initial garbled/short lines and overflow markers |\n\n---\n\n### **8. EMBEDDING INFRASTRUCTURE**\n\n**File:** `/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/lib/text-classifier/embedder.ts`\n\n```typescript\nMODEL_NAME = \"Xenova/all-MiniLM-L6-v2\"  // 384-dim vectors, normalized\nloadEmbedder()     // Async load transformer pipeline\nembedText()        // Generate embedding with mean pooling + normalization\n```\n\n**File:** `/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/lib/text-classifier/embeddings.ts`\n\n```typescript\ncosineSimilarity()  // Dot product (vectors normalized)\nSIMILARITY_THRESHOLD = 0.453  // For tag classification (not used in title extraction)\n```\n\n---\n\n### **9. TEST INFRASTRUCTURE**\n\n**File:** `/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/lib/text-classifier/__tests__/title-extractor.test.ts` (200+ lines)\n\n**Mock embed function:** Maps known words to predictable vectors\n- titleWords → [0.9, 0.1, 0]\n- headerWords → [0.1, 0.9, 0]\n- Neutral → [0.3, 0.3, 0.7]\n\n**Test coverage:**\n- Empty input\n- Title vs section header distinction\n- ALL_CAPS preservation\n- 2-line/3-line joins\n- Multi-title pages\n- Garbled line skipping\n- Bilingual pages\n\n---\n\n### **10. EVALUATION LOOP**\n\n**Files:**\n- `/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/title-loop.py` (1,262 lines) - Main self-improvement loop\n- `/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/eval_only.py` (92 lines) - Standalone evaluator\n\n**Infrastructure:**\n\n1. **Input files:** `/tools/title-loop/input/*.real.txt` and `*.generated.txt`\n2. **Extract via:** `npx tsx tools/title-loop/extract-title.ts <file>`\n3. **Matching logic:**\n   - Normalize: whitespace, hyphens→spaces, uppercase\n   - Strip Polish diacritics (ą→a, ć→c, etc.)\n   - Apply OCR substitution (0→o, 1→i, €→e)\n   - Check if expected parts all appear in extracted (handles multi-title with +)\n\n4. **Evaluation metrics:**\n   - Real files accuracy\n   - Generated files accuracy\n   - Combined accuracy\n\n5. **Loop phases:**\n   - Evaluate\n   - Analyze (Claude feedback)\n   - Plan (Improvement plan)\n   - Decompose (Break into tasks)\n   - Execute (Run tasks)\n   - Review\n   - Commit\n\n**Current state:** Iteration 28 (as of git log `e7e3098`)\n\n---\n\n### **KEY ALGORITHM INSIGHTS**\n\n1. **Three-way embedding scoring:** Penalizes both header and noise similarity, not just maximizing title similarity\n\n2. **Structural heading prioritization:** Uses embedding quality (rawScore), not position, to identify recipe headings\n\n3. **Position-based multiplier:** Early candidates get 1.0-1.24x boost, dampens after 50%, never dominates raw signal\n\n4. **Threshold calculation:** Based on best candidate's thresholdScore (excludes structural bonus) × 0.7, min 0.08\n\n5. **Multi-recipe detection:** Checks for ≥2 ALL_CAPS with vocabulary corroboration; distinguishes from single-recipe sub-sections\n\n6. **Bilingual handling:** Detects via embedding similarity or layout (position 0 + position 1-2 word mismatch)\n\n7. **Dedup priority:** Shorter wins, except compound titles and multi-line joins with category suffixes\n\n8. **Fallback to position:** Only when embedding provides no clear signal; relaxes rawScore for early positions\n\n9. **Corroboration check:** Vocabulary of candidate must appear elsewhere in document (prevents orphaned OCR artifacts)\n\n10. **OCR-resilient matching:** Handles digit→letter confusion, diacritics, and Cyrillic corruption\n\n---\n\n### **FILE LOCATIONS**\n\n```\nlib/text-classifier/\n├── title-extractor.ts          (1,665 lines - main implementation)\n├── embedder.ts                 (40 lines - MiniLM pipeline)\n├── embeddings.ts               (67 lines - similarity & threshold)\n├── food-dictionary.ts          (147 lines - Polish/English words)\n├── __tests__/\n│   └── title-extractor.test.ts (200+ lines - unit tests)\n\ntools/title-loop/\n├── extract-title.ts            (48 lines - CLI wrapper)\n├── title-loop.py               (1,262 lines - main evaluation loop)\n├── eval_only.py                (92 lines - standalone eval)\n├── docs/iter.txt               (iteration log)\n├── docs/28-e7e3098/            (iteration 28 results)\n└── input/                       (real & generated test files)\n```\n\nThis is a highly sophisticated, multilayered pipeline designed for robustness across OCR corruption, multilingual content, and complex recipe document layouts."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a2c72fce6cbb7cd9d (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 133532\ntool_uses: 20\nduration_ms: 120545</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c37a3300-1904-44e6-bf34-65ba8b38fada","uuid":"8b8efdad-70e3-4f04-ad16-4b114cbf411e","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Read the complete title extraction implementation. Be very thorough:\n\n1. Read lib/text-classifier/title-extractor.ts (the main file)\n2. Search for any related files in lib/text-classifier/ that the title extractor depends on\n3. Read any types, constants, or utility files used by the title extractor\n4. Look for embedding-related code (MiniLM, similarity scoring)\n5. Read the eval/test infrastructure in tools/title-loop/ to understand how the algorithm is evaluated\n\nI need to understand the full pipeline: candidate generation, scoring, filtering, and final selection.","agentId":"a2c72fce6cbb7cd9d","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Excellent! Now I have a comprehensive understanding of the system. Let me create a detailed summary:\n\n## Complete Title Extraction Implementation Analysis\n\nI've conducted a thorough analysis of the title extraction implementation. Here's the complete pipeline:\n\n---\n\n### **1. MAIN ENTRY POINT**\n**File:** `/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/lib/text-classifier/title-extractor.ts` (1,665 lines)\n\n**Two modes:**\n- `extractTitle()` - Fast synchronous heuristic fallback (finds first non-filtered line)\n- `extractTitleWithEmbeddings()` - Full semantic pipeline with MiniLM embeddings\n\n---\n\n### **2. CANDIDATE GENERATION PIPELINE**\n\n#### **2.1 Build Candidates (`buildCandidates` function, lines 537-731)**\n\n**Input:** Array of text lines\n\n**Steps:**\n\n1. **Collect non-empty lines** with original indices\n2. **Find burst end** - Skip initial preamble of garbled/short lines\n3. **Pre-join hyphen-broken lines** - \"ROASTED CHICKEN-\" + \"ABLES\" → single line\n4. **Pre-merge ALL_CAPS sequences** - Group consecutive short ALL_CAPS fragments into one candidate\n5. **Pre-merge continuation lines** - Lines starting with `/&+:(` get merged with preceding line\n6. **Build candidate pool**:\n   - Single-line candidates (after OCR repair)\n   - Blind OCR variants for early-position candidates (with digit→letter substitution)\n   - 2-line joins\n   - 3-line joins\n   - Deduplication via lowercase normalization\n\n7. **Pre-filter to 25 candidates** - Keep ALL_CAPS and short ones first\n\n**Output:** Up to 25 candidates with `{ text, position, origin }`\n\n#### **2.2 Hard Filters (`passesHardFilters`, lines 385-426)**\n\nCandidate must NOT be:\n- Outside 3-80 character range\n- Ingredient line (measurement units, quantities)\n- Starting with a number or fraction\n- Recipe metadata (serving sizes, prep times, Polish/English patterns)\n- Garbled (low/high vowel ratio, internal caps, isolated short words)\n- Cooking instruction (English/Polish verb starts)\n- Pipe-separated or trailing page numbers\n- Multiple slashes (navigation breadcrumbs)\n- Bullet points\n- Section labels (INGREDIENTS, SKŁADNIKI, etc.)\n- 8+ words without separators (body text)\n- Known non-title words (single words: \"the\", \"and\", etc.)\n\n---\n\n### **3. SCORING SYSTEM**\n\n#### **3.1 Reference Embeddings (Semantic Anchors)**\n\nThree reference phrases:\n```\nTITLE_REFERENCE = \"recipe name, dish title, name of the food, nazwa przepisu, nazwa dania\"\nHEADER_REFERENCE = \"ingredients list, cooking directions, section heading, składniki, przygotowanie, sposób wykonania\"\nNOISE_REFERENCE = \"page number, table of contents, book footer, garbled text\"\n```\n\n#### **3.2 Raw Score Calculation (Pass 1, lines 1025-1034)**\n\nFor each candidate:\n```\nembedding = embed(candidate_text)\ntitleSim = cosineSimilarity(embedding, titleRefEmbedding)\nheaderSim = cosineSimilarity(embedding, headerRefEmbedding)\nnoiseSim = cosineSimilarity(embedding, noiseRefEmbedding)\nrawScore = titleSim - Math.max(headerSim, noiseSim)\n```\n\n**Logic:** Maximize title similarity while penalizing header/noise resemblance.\n\n#### **3.3 Structural Heading Detection (lines 1019-1086)**\n\nSelect best ALL_CAPS candidate (≥2 words, ≥4 alpha chars per word):\n- Ranked by `rawScore`\n- Check for truncation artifacts (e.g., \"FRON\" vs \"SAFFRON\")\n- Find continuation joins (with `/&+:(` prefix on next line)\n\n#### **3.4 Bonus System (Pass 2, lines 1089-1189)**\n\nApplied to all candidates:\n\n| Bonus | Trigger | Amount | Notes |\n|-------|---------|--------|-------|\n| **ALL_CAPS bonus** | ALL_CAPS text with ≥4 letters | +0.08 (multi-word) or +0.03 (single-word) | Single words get reduced bonus (likely section labels) |\n| **Structural bonus** | Best ALL_CAPS heading or its continuation | +0.10 | Applied to `firstStructuralHeading` |\n| **Position factor** | Candidate rank in pool | 1.0 to 1.24x multiplier | Earlier candidates get 1.0-1.24x boost; dampens after 50% |\n| **Preamble bonus** | First candidate after filtered/empty lines | +0.08 or +0.12 | Higher if preamble had structural markers |\n| **Direct-successor bonus** | Top 3 candidates following section label/metadata | +0.10 | Fires independently of first-after-preamble |\n\n**Capped positional boost:** All positional bonuses combined ≤ +0.15\n\n**Three score variants:**\n- `rawScore` - Pure embedding signal (≥-0.05 for early pos, ≥0.02 for later)\n- `baseScore` - rawScore + allCapsBonus + structuralBonus (diagnostics)\n- `thresholdScore` - rawScore + allCapsBonus (excludes structural, prevents inflation on multi-recipe pages)\n- `score` - rawScore × positionFactor + allCapsBonus + structuralBonus (final ranking)\n\n---\n\n### **4. MULTI-TITLE & BILINGUAL DETECTION**\n\n#### **4.1 Bilingual Title Suppression (lines 1191-1276)**\n\n**Pattern 1: Mixed-case + ALL_CAPS pair**\n- Detect if position-0 mixed-case candidate is followed by ALL_CAPS at position ≤2\n- Check embedding similarity (>0.4 cosine) or word-overlap non-matching\n- Suppress translation candidates from threshold calculation\n\n**Pattern 2: ALL_CAPS translation reassignment**\n- If structural heading is identified as translation, reassign it to non-translation alternative\n\n**Pattern 3: Subtitle suppression**\n- Short mixed-case at position 0 + longer mixed-case at position 1-2 with >2 extra words\n- Apply -0.15 penalty to longer one\n\n**Pattern 4: Mixed-case + mixed-case bilingual layout**\n- Position 0: ≤2 words\n- Position 1-2: 2-5 words, mixed-case, not ingredient/instruction\n- Section label nearby (within 6 lines)\n- Boost position-0 candidate by +0.15\n\n#### **4.2 Threshold Calculation (lines 1359-1362)**\n\n```\nbestThresholdScore = max(scoredForThreshold[*].thresholdScore)\nthreshold = max(0.08, bestThresholdScore × 0.7)\n```\n\n**Selects:** Candidates with `score >= threshold`\n\n#### **4.3 Fallback Logic (lines 1367-1381)**\n\nIf threshold filters all candidates:\n- Use best positional candidate\n- Relax `rawScore` requirement for position ≤2 (≥-0.05) vs position >2 (≥0.02)\n\n#### **4.4 Title-Absent Page Guard (lines 1383-1391)**\n\nWhen first 3 non-empty lines are all ingredients/instructions/prose:\n- Require `rawScore >= 0.10` (strict)\n- Discard candidates beyond position 2\n\n---\n\n### **5. DEDUPLICATION & MULTI-TITLE LOGIC**\n\n#### **5.1 Pre-dedup Filters**\n\n1. **Structural heading prefix removal** (lines 1393-1408)\n   - Remove space-delimited prefixes of `firstStructuralHeading` if heading itself passed threshold\n\n2. **Continuation join protection** (lines 1410-1442)\n   - Protect 2-line/3-line joins from being removed by their single-line prefix/suffix\n\n3. **Sub-section header removal** (lines 1444-1465)\n   - Remove ALL_CAPS followed by ingredients if longer candidate contains it\n\n4. **Multi-line join component protection** (lines 1467-1485)\n   - If \"Lamb Stew\" (join) survives AND both \"Lamb\" + \"Stew\" (singles) survive, remove singles\n\n5. **Position-0 compound protection** (lines 1487-1503)\n   - Remove shorter candidates >10 lines away from position-0 compound if contained in it\n\n#### **5.2 Core Dedup Rule (lines 1505-1534)**\n\n**\"Shorter wins\":** If candidate A is a substring of candidate B, remove A\n- EXCEPTION: Compound titles with `[+:&]` separators protected\n- EXCEPTION: Multi-line join with food-category label suffix protected (e.g., \"LEMON HERB ROASTED VEGETABLES\")\n\n#### **5.3 Multi-Title Selection (lines 1536-1618)**\n\n**For ≥2 survivors:**\n\n- **≥2 ALL_CAPS:** Multi-recipe page. Use corroborated candidates (vocabulary support in document). Check if non-first headings are sub-headers (followed by ingredients) → if so, keep only first.\n- **1 ALL_CAPS:** Check relative position. If in last 25% of document, prefer earlier candidates (likely category footer).\n- **0 ALL_CAPS:** Mixed-case page. If span >10 lines, apply positional tiebreak (keep earliest high-scorer). If ≤10 lines span, keep all (genuine multi-recipe).\n\n**Final:** Cap at 3, join with \" + \"\n\n---\n\n### **6. OCR REPAIR**\n\n#### **6.1 Dictionary-Guided Repair (`repairOcrWord`, lines 773-801)**\n\n**Substitution map:**\n```\n\"0\" → \"o\", \"1\" → [\"i\", \"l\"], \"4\" → \"a\", \"5\" → \"s\"\n\"¡\" → \"i\", \"í\" → [\"i\", \"l\"], \"€\" → \"e\"\n```\n\n**Process:** Generate all combinations and check against FOOD_DICTIONARY (Polish + English ingredients, cooking terms, adjectives)\n\n#### **6.2 Blind OCR Repair (`applyBlindOcrRepair`, lines 875-890)**\n\nUsed for early-position candidates with artifacts:\n- ALL_CAPS: 1→I, 0→O, 4→A, 5→S\n- Mixed-case: 1→i (default) or 1→l (fallback), plus special cases for ¡/€\n\n#### **6.3 Erratic Casing Normalization (lines 892-912)**\n\nDetect words with ≥2 internal caps and ≥30% lowercase → capitalize first, lowercase rest\n\n#### **6.4 Post-Processing (`normalizeOcrTitle`, lines 946-976)**\n\n1. Dictionary repair\n2. Strip trailing section markers (+ SERVING AND STORAGE:, etc.)\n3. Blind OCR character substitution\n4. Title-case conversion (only if substitution changed the text)\n5. Normalize erratic casing\n\n---\n\n### **7. HELPER FILTERS & DETECTORS**\n\n| Function | Purpose |\n|----------|---------|\n| `looksLikeIngredient()` | Detect measurement units or \"to taste\" |\n| `startsWithNumber()` | Detect numbered lists |\n| `isAllCaps()` | Case detection |\n| `looksLikeMetadata()` | SERVES, PREP TIME, DLA, GODZ, etc. |\n| `isLikelyGarbled()` | Vowel ratio, pipes, Cyrillic, caps transitions, etc. |\n| `looksLikeCookingInstruction()` | English/Polish verb starts (beat, fold, smaż, etc.) |\n| `isSectionLabel()` | INGREDIENTS, SKŁADNIKI, WARZYWA, etc. |\n| `isBodyProse()` | Lowercase-start + 4+ words |\n| `isTitleAbsentPage()` | First 3 lines all ingredients/instructions |\n| `passesCorroboration()` | Vocabulary support check (≥67% or 100% for ≤3 words) |\n| `findBurstEnd()` | Skip initial garbled/short lines and overflow markers |\n\n---\n\n### **8. EMBEDDING INFRASTRUCTURE**\n\n**File:** `/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/lib/text-classifier/embedder.ts`\n\n```typescript\nMODEL_NAME = \"Xenova/all-MiniLM-L6-v2\"  // 384-dim vectors, normalized\nloadEmbedder()     // Async load transformer pipeline\nembedText()        // Generate embedding with mean pooling + normalization\n```\n\n**File:** `/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/lib/text-classifier/embeddings.ts`\n\n```typescript\ncosineSimilarity()  // Dot product (vectors normalized)\nSIMILARITY_THRESHOLD = 0.453  // For tag classification (not used in title extraction)\n```\n\n---\n\n### **9. TEST INFRASTRUCTURE**\n\n**File:** `/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/lib/text-classifier/__tests__/title-extractor.test.ts` (200+ lines)\n\n**Mock embed function:** Maps known words to predictable vectors\n- titleWords → [0.9, 0.1, 0]\n- headerWords → [0.1, 0.9, 0]\n- Neutral → [0.3, 0.3, 0.7]\n\n**Test coverage:**\n- Empty input\n- Title vs section header distinction\n- ALL_CAPS preservation\n- 2-line/3-line joins\n- Multi-title pages\n- Garbled line skipping\n- Bilingual pages\n\n---\n\n### **10. EVALUATION LOOP**\n\n**Files:**\n- `/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/title-loop.py` (1,262 lines) - Main self-improvement loop\n- `/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/eval_only.py` (92 lines) - Standalone evaluator\n\n**Infrastructure:**\n\n1. **Input files:** `/tools/title-loop/input/*.real.txt` and `*.generated.txt`\n2. **Extract via:** `npx tsx tools/title-loop/extract-title.ts <file>`\n3. **Matching logic:**\n   - Normalize: whitespace, hyphens→spaces, uppercase\n   - Strip Polish diacritics (ą→a, ć→c, etc.)\n   - Apply OCR substitution (0→o, 1→i, €→e)\n   - Check if expected parts all appear in extracted (handles multi-title with +)\n\n4. **Evaluation metrics:**\n   - Real files accuracy\n   - Generated files accuracy\n   - Combined accuracy\n\n5. **Loop phases:**\n   - Evaluate\n   - Analyze (Claude feedback)\n   - Plan (Improvement plan)\n   - Decompose (Break into tasks)\n   - Execute (Run tasks)\n   - Review\n   - Commit\n\n**Current state:** Iteration 28 (as of git log `e7e3098`)\n\n---\n\n### **KEY ALGORITHM INSIGHTS**\n\n1. **Three-way embedding scoring:** Penalizes both header and noise similarity, not just maximizing title similarity\n\n2. **Structural heading prioritization:** Uses embedding quality (rawScore), not position, to identify recipe headings\n\n3. **Position-based multiplier:** Early candidates get 1.0-1.24x boost, dampens after 50%, never dominates raw signal\n\n4. **Threshold calculation:** Based on best candidate's thresholdScore (excludes structural bonus) × 0.7, min 0.08\n\n5. **Multi-recipe detection:** Checks for ≥2 ALL_CAPS with vocabulary corroboration; distinguishes from single-recipe sub-sections\n\n6. **Bilingual handling:** Detects via embedding similarity or layout (position 0 + position 1-2 word mismatch)\n\n7. **Dedup priority:** Shorter wins, except compound titles and multi-line joins with category suffixes\n\n8. **Fallback to position:** Only when embedding provides no clear signal; relaxes rawScore for early positions\n\n9. **Corroboration check:** Vocabulary of candidate must appear elsewhere in document (prevents orphaned OCR artifacts)\n\n10. **OCR-resilient matching:** Handles digit→letter confusion, diacritics, and Cyrillic corruption\n\n---\n\n### **FILE LOCATIONS**\n\n```\nlib/text-classifier/\n├── title-extractor.ts          (1,665 lines - main implementation)\n├── embedder.ts                 (40 lines - MiniLM pipeline)\n├── embeddings.ts               (67 lines - similarity & threshold)\n├── food-dictionary.ts          (147 lines - Polish/English words)\n├── __tests__/\n│   └── title-extractor.test.ts (200+ lines - unit tests)\n\ntools/title-loop/\n├── extract-title.ts            (48 lines - CLI wrapper)\n├── title-loop.py               (1,262 lines - main evaluation loop)\n├── eval_only.py                (92 lines - standalone eval)\n├── docs/iter.txt               (iteration log)\n├── docs/28-e7e3098/            (iteration 28 results)\n└── input/                       (real & generated test files)\n```\n\nThis is a highly sophisticated, multilayered pipeline designed for robustness across OCR corruption, multilingual content, and complex recipe document layouts."}],"totalDurationMs":120545,"totalTokens":133532,"totalToolUseCount":20,"usage":{"input_tokens":3,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1250,"cache_read_input_tokens":127947,"output_tokens":4332,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,