{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01QfshFfmsxfsi5A5VTkp7Dn","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Task 03: Add direct-successor bonus for candidates immediately following section headers\n     2→\n     3→## Summary\n     4→\n     5→Add a scoring bonus for candidates whose immediately preceding line is a section header, metadata, or pipe-separated line, improving extraction when a category/section header precedes the title.\n     6→\n     7→## Files to modify\n     8→\n     9→- `lib/text-classifier/title-extractor.ts`\n    10→\n    11→## Changes\n    12→\n    13→### Add direct-successor bonus in the scoring pass (~after line 1055)\n    14→\n    15→After the existing first-after-preamble bonus logic (which ends at line 1055 with the `maxPositionalBoost` cap), add a new \"direct-successor\" bonus. This bonus fires when the line immediately before a candidate is a section header or metadata line, regardless of what preceded that header.\n    16→\n    17→The existing first-after-preamble bonus (lines 1024-1044) requires ALL preceding lines to be filtered/empty. The direct-successor bonus is complementary: it only checks the immediately preceding line.\n    18→\n    19→Insert after the `maxPositionalBoost` cap block (after line 1055):\n    20→\n    21→```typescript\n    22→  // Direct-successor bonus: when the line immediately before this candidate is a\n    23→  // section label, metadata, or pipe-separated line, the candidate is very likely\n    24→  // the title that follows that header. This complements the first-after-preamble\n    25→  // bonus which requires ALL preceding lines to be filtered — this one fires even\n    26→  // when earlier non-filtered lines exist.\n    27→  for (let ci = 0; ci < scored.length && ci <= 2; ci++) {\n    28→    const candidate = scored[ci];\n    29→    if (candidate.position > 0) {\n    30→      const prevLine = lines[candidate.position - 1]?.trim() ?? \"\";\n    31→      const prevIsHeader = isSectionLabel(prevLine) ||\n    32→                           looksLikeMetadata(prevLine) ||\n    33→                           prevLine.includes(\" | \");\n    34→      if (prevIsHeader) {\n    35→        candidate.score += 0.10;\n    36→        candidate.baseScore += 0.10;\n    37→        candidate.thresholdScore += 0.10;\n    38→      }\n    39→    }\n    40→  }\n    41→```\n    42→\n    43→Important details:\n    44→- The loop uses `ci <= 2` to limit to the first 3 candidates (by score order, since `scored` is sorted by score descending). This prevents the bonus from firing on random mid-document candidates.\n    45→- The bonus is +0.10, which stacks with the first-after-preamble bonus but both are constrained by the overall scoring dynamics.\n    46→- `isSectionLabel` (line 190) checks against `SECTION_LABELS` set (ingredients, directions, etc. in English/Polish)\n    47→- `looksLikeMetadata` (line 226) checks `METADATA_PATTERNS` (serves/makes/yields, times)\n    48→- The `prevLine.includes(\" | \")` check catches pipe-separated metadata like `Lato | Zupy | DLA 4 OSÓB`\n    49→- All three score components (`score`, `baseScore`, `thresholdScore`) are incremented to maintain consistency with how other bonuses work\n    50→\n    51→Note: The `maxPositionalBoost` cap (line 1048) only applies to the first candidate's combined preamble + position bonus. The direct-successor bonus is a separate mechanism. If stacking becomes an issue in eval, the bonus value (0.10) can be tuned down.\n    52→\n    53→## Verification\n    54→\n    55→1. Run eval and check that the 3 Pattern 2 cases improve:\n    56→   - Halibut with Saffron Cream Sauce (preceded by \"FISH & SEAFOOD\" section header)\n    57→   - Roasted Asparagus with Parmesan (preceded by section header)\n    58→   - Ogórkowa Zupa (preceded by pipe-separated metadata `Lato | Zupy | DLA 4 OSÓB | ...`)\n    59→2. Verify no regressions on cases that already have section headers preceding titles (these should only get better or stay the same)\n    60→3. Check that the bonus doesn't fire on mid-document candidates (the `ci <= 2` guard)\n    61→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01Pn2J9YHaerVj5dEWKNBP49","session_id":"c37a3300-1904-44e6-bf34-65ba8b38fada","uuid":"98ddaff8-2ccb-439f-af17-0ad6147b7132"}
