{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01XMAbdatGzshWgvz9U1Pz1D","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→Lato | Zupy | DLA 4 OSÓB | PRZYGOTOWANIE 15 MIN | GOTOWANIE 20 MIN\n     2→\n     3→OGÓRKOWA ZUPA\n     4→\n     5→Ogórkowa zupa, or Polish cucumber soup, is a refreshing summer soup served\n     6→either hot or cold. The dill-infused broth is bright and tangy, perfect for\n     7→warm days when you want something light yet satisfying and nourishing.\n     8→\n     9→INGREDIENTS:\n    10→- 6 medium cucumbers, peeled and diced\n    11→- 6 cups vegetable or chicken stock\n    12→- 1 large onion, diced\n    13→- 2 tbsp butter\n    14→- 2 cloves garlic, minced\n    15→- 3 tbsp fresh dill, chopped\n    16→- 2 tbsp fresh lemon juice\n    17→- 1/2 cup sour cream\n    18→- 1/4 tsp white pepper\n    19→- Salt to taste\n    20→- Fresh dill sprigs for garnish\n    21→\n    22→INSTRUCTIONS:\n    23→1. In a large pot, melt butter over medium heat.\n    24→2. Sauté diced onion until translucent, about 5 minutes.\n    25→3. Add minced garlic and cook 1 minute more.\n    26→4. Add diced cucumbers and cook for 3 minutes, stirring occasionally.\n    27→5. Pour in vegetable or chicken stock and bring to a simmer.\n    28→6. Simmer for 15 minutes until cucumbers are tender.\n    29→7. Add fresh dill and lemon juice.\n    30→8. Season with salt and white pepper to taste.\n    31→9. For creamy version, stir in sour cream just before serving.\n    32→10. Serve hot in winter or chill thoroughly and serve cold.\n    33→\n    34→SERVING SUGGESTIONS:\n    35→Top with dollop of sour cream and fresh dill sprig. Serve with dark rye bread.\n    36→Can be made 1 day ahead and stored in refrigerator.\n    37→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01Pn2J9YHaerVj5dEWKNBP49","session_id":"c37a3300-1904-44e6-bf34-65ba8b38fada","uuid":"495b2334-9070-404f-8d41-428b3bd1a528"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Q4QXCrbWhREAWekZTqdWFH","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→Reduce heat and stir in the remaining stock, one ladle at a time, until the rice is\n     2→creamy but still al dente, about 18-20 minutes. The risotto should flow slightly on the plate.\n     3→Season with salt and white pepper. Finish with butter and grated Parmigiano-Reggiano.\n     4→\n     5→CARPACCIO DI PESCE SPADA\n     6→\n     7→Slice the swordfish paper-thin. Arrange on chilled plates. Dress with extra virgin olive oil,\n     8→lemon juice, and sea salt. Scatter thinly shaved fennel and microgreens. Serve immediately.\n     9→\n    10→Preparation: 10 minutes\n    11→Serves: 4\n    12→\n    13→CARPACCIO WITH CITRUS DRESSING\n    14→\n    15→Place thin slices on a cold plate. Whisk together lemon, lime, orange juice with good quality\n    16→oil. Season with fıne sea salt and crushed coriander seeds. Garnish with fresh herbs and\n    17→thinly sliced radish.\n    18→\n    19→nto a loured work counter and knead until smooth, approx 8 minutes. Proof in oiled bowl, cover\n    20→with damp cloth, 45 minutes at room temperature. Shape into ½ dozen rounds. Second proof 30 min.\n    21→\n    22→Place pans in 225°C/435-VI0.. oven for 12-15 minutes until golden brown. Cool on wire rack.\n    23→\n    24→Makes: 1 dozen\n    25→\n    26→FRESH PASTA DOUGH\n    27→\n    28→125 grams plain flour\n    29→½ cup plus ı tablespoon water\n    30→Pinch of sea salt\n    31→\n    32→Combine flour and slt on work bench. Make well in center. Add water gradually, mixing with fork\n    33→until dough comes together. Knead 5 minutes.\n    34→\n    35→Mushroom Risotto\n    36→\n    37→Ingredients:\n    38→300g arborio rice\n    39→1 liter vegetable stock\n    40→250g mixed mushrooms, sliced\n    41→1 medium onion, finely diced\n    42→100ml dry white wine\n    43→50g butter\n    44→50g parmesan cheese, grated\n    45→2 tablespoons olive oil\n    46→Salt and white pepper to taste\n    47→Fresh parsley for garnish\n    48→\n    49→Method:\n    50→Heat stock in separate pan and keep at gentle simmer. Heat olive oil in large risotto pan over\n    51→medium heat. Sauté onion until translucent, about 3 minutes. Add mushrooms and cook until\n    52→golden, approximately 5 minutes. Add rice and stir constantly for 2 minutes to toast grains.\n    53→\n    54→Deglaze with white wine and stir until absorbed. Begin adding warm stock one ladle at a time,\n    55→stirring frequently. Each addition should be absorbed before adding more stock, taking about\n    56→18-20 minutes total. The rice should be creamy yet retain a slight firmness to the bite.\n    57→\n    58→Finish risotto by stirring in butter and grated parmesan cheese. Season with salt and white\n    59→pepper to taste. Transfer to serving bowl and garnish with fresh parsley and additional cheese.\n    60→\n    61→Serves: 4-6\n    62→Preparation time: 10 minutes\n    63→Cooking time: 30 minutes\n    64→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01Pn2J9YHaerVj5dEWKNBP49","session_id":"c37a3300-1904-44e6-bf34-65ba8b38fada","uuid":"42b4e3c2-76eb-4248-9e54-e3bac32c4912"}
