{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01VLsNGMxpVXZ3CzB8677Mh7","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Task 01: Dual-variant blind OCR repair with erratic casing normalization\n     2→\n     3→## Summary\n     4→\n     5→Replace the single-output `applyBlindOcrRepair` with a multi-variant generator that produces both `1→i` and `1→l` candidates, and add erratic-casing normalization for lines like `KoPyTka`.\n     6→\n     7→## Files to modify\n     8→\n     9→- `lib/text-classifier/title-extractor.ts`\n    10→\n    11→## Changes\n    12→\n    13→### Part A: Add `generateBlindOcrVariants` function\n    14→\n    15→Add a new function after `applyBlindOcrRepair` (after line ~862) that generates both `i` and `l` variants:\n    16→\n    17→```typescript\n    18→/**\n    19→ * Generate multiple blind OCR repair variants for embedding comparison.\n    20→ * For ALL_CAPS text, returns a single variant (1→I is unambiguous).\n    21→ * For mixed-case text, returns two variants: one with 1→i and one with 1→l,\n    22→ * letting the embedding scorer pick the better one.\n    23→ */\n    24→function generateBlindOcrVariants(text: string): Array<string> {\n    25→  if (isAllCaps(text)) {\n    26→    // ALL_CAPS: single variant, same as current applyBlindOcrRepair\n    27→    const repaired = applyBlindOcrRepair(text);\n    28→    return repaired !== text ? [repaired] : [];\n    29→  }\n    30→\n    31→  const variants: Array<string> = [];\n    32→\n    33→  // i-variant: 1→i between lowercase letters\n    34→  const iVariant = text.split(/(\\s+)/).map((token) => {\n    35→    if (/^\\s+$/.test(token)) return token;\n    36→    if (isAllCaps(token) && token.length > 1) {\n    37→      return token\n    38→        .replace(/1/g, \"I\")\n    39→        .replace(/0(?=[A-Z])/g, \"O\")\n    40→        .replace(/(?<=[A-Z])0/g, \"O\");\n    41→    }\n    42→    return token\n    43→      .replace(/(?<=[a-zà-ż])1/g, \"i\")\n    44→      .replace(/1(?=[a-zà-ż])/g, \"i\")\n    45→      .replace(/¡/g, \"i\")\n    46→      .replace(/€/g, \"e\");\n    47→  }).join(\"\");\n    48→\n    49→  // l-variant: 1→l between lowercase letters (current behavior)\n    50→  const lVariant = applyBlindOcrRepair(text);\n    51→\n    52→  if (iVariant !== text) variants.push(iVariant);\n    53→  if (lVariant !== text && lVariant !== iVariant) variants.push(lVariant);\n    54→\n    55→  return variants;\n    56→}\n    57→```\n    58→\n    59→### Part B: Add erratic-casing detection and normalization\n    60→\n    61→Add these two functions near the OCR repair utilities (before `generateBlindOcrVariants`):\n    62→\n    63→```typescript\n    64→function hasErraticCasing(text: string): boolean {\n    65→  return text.split(/\\s+/).some(word => {\n    66→    if (word.length < 3) return false;\n    67→    if (isAllCaps(word)) return false;\n    68→    // Check for uppercase letters after position 0 that aren't part of known patterns\n    69→    const inner = word.slice(1);\n    70→    const upperInner = (inner.match(/[A-ZÀ-Ż]/g) || []).length;\n    71→    const lowerInner = (inner.match(/[a-zà-ż]/g) || []).length;\n    72→    return upperInner >= 2 && upperInner >= lowerInner * 0.3;\n    73→  });\n    74→}\n    75→\n    76→function normalizeErraticCasing(text: string): string {\n    77→  return text.split(/(\\s+)/).map(token => {\n    78→    if (/^\\s+$/.test(token)) return token;\n    79→    if (isAllCaps(token)) return token;\n    80→    if (hasErraticCasing(token)) {\n    81→      return token.charAt(0).toUpperCase() + token.slice(1).toLowerCase();\n    82→    }\n    83→    return token;\n    84→  }).join(\"\");\n    85→}\n    86→```\n    87→\n    88→### Part C: Update the OCR repair block in `buildCandidates`\n    89→\n    90→Replace the existing blind OCR repair block at lines ~658-671:\n    91→\n    92→**Current code:**\n    93→```typescript\n    94→    if (line.index <= 5 && OCR_ARTIFACT_PATTERN.test(line.text)) {\n    95→      const blindRepaired = applyBlindOcrRepair(singleText);\n    96→      if (blindRepaired !== singleText && passesHardFilters(blindRepaired)) {\n    97→        const norm = blindRepaired.toLowerCase();\n    98→        if (!seen.has(norm)) {\n    99→          seen.add(norm);\n   100→          candidates.push({ text: blindRepaired, position: line.index, origin: \"single\" });\n   101→        }\n   102→      }\n   103→    }\n   104→```\n   105→\n   106→**New code:**\n   107→```typescript\n   108→    if (line.index <= 5 && (OCR_ARTIFACT_PATTERN.test(line.text) || hasErraticCasing(line.text))) {\n   109→      let repairable = singleText;\n   110→      if (hasErraticCasing(repairable)) {\n   111→        repairable = normalizeErraticCasing(repairable);\n   112→      }\n   113→      const variants = generateBlindOcrVariants(repairable);\n   114→      for (const variant of variants) {\n   115→        if (variant !== singleText && passesHardFilters(variant)) {\n   116→          const norm = variant.toLowerCase();\n   117→          if (!seen.has(norm)) {\n   118→            seen.add(norm);\n   119→            candidates.push({ text: variant, position: line.index, origin: \"single\" });\n   120→          }\n   121→        }\n   122→      }\n   123→    }\n   124→```\n   125→\n   126→Note: Also add the erratic-casing-only path — when there are no OCR artifacts but casing is erratic, the normalized text itself should be added as a candidate:\n   127→\n   128→```typescript\n   129→    if (line.index <= 5 && (OCR_ARTIFACT_PATTERN.test(line.text) || hasErraticCasing(line.text))) {\n   130→      let repairable = singleText;\n   131→      if (hasErraticCasing(repairable)) {\n   132→        repairable = normalizeErraticCasing(repairable);\n   133→        // Add the casing-normalized version as a candidate even without OCR repair\n   134→        if (repairable !== singleText && passesHardFilters(repairable)) {\n   135→          const norm = repairable.toLowerCase();\n   136→          if (!seen.has(norm)) {\n   137→            seen.add(norm);\n   138→            candidates.push({ text: repairable, position: line.index, origin: \"single\" });\n   139→          }\n   140→        }\n   141→      }\n   142→      const variants = generateBlindOcrVariants(repairable);\n   143→      for (const variant of variants) {\n   144→        if (variant !== singleText && variant !== repairable && passesHardFilters(variant)) {\n   145→          const norm = variant.toLowerCase();\n   146→          if (!seen.has(norm)) {\n   147→            seen.add(norm);\n   148→            candidates.push({ text: variant, position: line.index, origin: \"single\" });\n   149→          }\n   150→        }\n   151→      }\n   152→    }\n   153→```\n   154→\n   155→## Verification\n   156→\n   157→Run the eval suite and check that these 6 test cases now pass:\n   158→- Braised Cod with White Wine\n   159→- Drożdże Sernik\n   160→- Piernik z Śliwkami\n   161→- Roasted Beet and Walnut Dip\n   162→- Żurek Krakowski\n   163→- Kopytka z Pieczarkami Leśnymi\n   164→\n   165→No regressions on previously passing tests. The extra candidates (at most ~5 additional) stay well within the 25-candidate cap.\n   166→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01Pn2J9YHaerVj5dEWKNBP49","session_id":"c37a3300-1904-44e6-bf34-65ba8b38fada","uuid":"71c3cce3-0a03-4b77-8af3-2e3324c6ec05"}
