tor.ts\n\n**Lines 1000-1200: Scoring System (with bonuses)**\n\nKey mechanisms:\n1. **Base scoring (lines 1025-1114):**\n   - Raw score: `titleSim - max(headerSim, noiseSim)` (embedding quality)\n   - ALL_CAPS bonus: +0.08 (multi-word), +0.03 (single word)\n   - Structural heading bonus: +0.10 (best ALL_CAPS heading)\n   - Position factor: multiplicative, up to +12% for early candidates\n\n2. **First-after-preamble bonus (lines 1121-1149):**\n   - When all lines before first candidate are filtered/empty, +0.12 (if preamble has structural markers) or +0.08\n   - Capped at +0.15 combined with other positional bonuses\n\n3. **Direct-successor bonus (lines 1150-1177):**\n   - When line immediately before candidate (or nearest non-empty if blank lines intervene) is section header/metadata: +0.10\n   - Only applied to top 3 candidates\n   - **BUG in iteration 28:** Doesn't skip blank lines—fixed in iteration 29 plan\n\n4. **Bilingual translation suppression (lines 1191-1246):**\n   - Detects mixed-case title at position 0 followed by similar ALL_CAPS at position ≤2\n   - Uses embedding similarity (>0.4) or layout-based word-overlap detection\n   - Suppresses translations before threshold computation to prevent inflation\n\n5. **Subtitle suppression (lines 1278-1289):**\n   - Short position-0 title followed by longer position-1-2 candidate: -0.15 penalty\n\n---\n\n### Lines 860-920: OCR Repair & Casing Normalization\n\n**Current implementation (after iteration 28 fixes):**\n\n```typescript\n// Lines 875-890: applyBlindOcrRepair\nfunction applyBlindOcrRepair(text: string): string {\n  if (isAllCaps(text)) {\n    return text\n      .replace(/1/g, \"I\")\n      .replace(/0(?=[A-ZÀ-Ż])/g, \"O\")  // before/after lookarounds\n      .replace(/(?<=[A-ZÀ-Ż])0/g, \"O\")\n      .replace(/4(?=[A-ZÀ-Ż])/g, \"A\")\n      .replace(/5(?=[A-ZÀ-Ż])/g, \"S\")  // digits to letters\n      .replace(/¡/g, \"I\")\n      .replace(/€/g, \"E\")\n      .replace(/[ÍÌ]/g, \"I\");\n  }\n  return applyBlindOcrRepairMixedCase(text, \"i\");  // BUG FIXED: was \"l\", now \"i\"\n}\n\n// Lines 892-901: Erratic casing detection\nfunction hasErraticCasing(text: string): boolean {\n  return text.split(/\\s+/).some(word => {\n    if (word.length < 3) return false;\n    if (isAllCaps(word)) return false;\n    const inner = word.slice(1);\n    const upperInner = (inner.match(/[A-ZÀ-Ż]/g) || []).length;\n    const lowerInner = (inner.match(/[a-zà-ż]/g) || []).length;\n    return upperInner >= 2 && upperInner >= lowerInner * 0.3;\n    // Catches KoPyTka (2 upper, 3 lower = 2 >= 0.9), exempts McDonald (1 upper, 7 lower = 1 < 2.1)\n  });\n}\n\n// Lines 903-912: Normalize erratic casing\nfunction normalizeErraticCasing(text: string): string {\n  return text.split(/(\\s+)/).map(token => {\n    if (/^\\s+$/.test(token)) return token;\n    if (isAllCaps(token)) return token;\n    if (hasErraticCasing(token)) {\n      return token.charAt(0).toUpperCase() + token.slice(1).toLowerCase();\n      // KoPyTka → Kopytka\n    }\n    return token;\n  }).join(\"\");\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### Iteration 29 Plan Fixes Summary\n\nThe 4 proposed fixes for iteration 29 are:\n\n1. **Dual-variant blind OCR repair** — Generate both `1→i` and `1→l` candidates; let embedding scorer pick\n   - Fixes: Braised Cod, Roasted Beet, Drożdże Sernik, Piernik z Śliwkami, Żurek Krakowski (5 cases)\n   - Plus erratic-casing normalization for Kopytka case (1 case)\n\n2. **Direct-successor bonus with blank-line skip** — Scan backward past blanks to find headers\n   - Fixes: Halibut, Ogórkowa Zupa (and likely Roasted Asparagus if it were in your list) (3 cases)\n\n3. **Broaden overflow marker regex** — Match `PREVIOUS\\s+(RECIPE|PAGE)` without requiring `OVERFLOW`, add `CORRUPTED\\s+(SECTION|TEXT)`, add `PARTIAL\\s+RECIPE`\n   - Fixes: Peach Cobbler (1 case)\n\n4. **Unified body-content prologue detector** — Interleave instruction + prose/continuation lines; threshold ≥3 total\n   - Fixes: Mushroom Risotto (1 case)\n\nAll