from a text that's already been rejected, so the variants won't help.\n\nWait, let me reconsider the blind OCR repair flow. When I apply the mixed-case repair to each token, \"Bra1sed\" becomes \"Braised\", \"w1th\" becomes \"with\", and so on, producing \"Braised Cod with White Wine\" — which should definitely pass the hard filters. But if the result is still empty, either that variant isn't being added as a candidate despite passing the filters, or it's being added but scoring too low to surface in the results. Let me check what's happening in the token-level repair logic. Looking at the mixed-case path, it only applies the `1→i` replacement through `applyBlindOcrRepairToken`, but the `0→o` handling seems to be missing entirely for non-uppercase contexts. The Pattern 7 failure confirms this — `0` isn't being converted in mixed-case words, only `1` is.\n\nSo the real puzzle is why Pattern 1 and Pattern 2 are failing when they only contain `1` substitutions, which should work. The blind OCR repair logic itself might not be the bottleneck here.\n\nLet me check what triggers the blind OCR variant generation in the first place — there's a condition checking the line index and whether it matches `OCR_ARTIFACT_PATTERN` or has erratic casing. I need to verify that these failing examples actually pass that gate to generate variants at all. And I'm realizing we're looking at the code from iteration 28, not 29 yet — so the improvement plan I need to create should address whatever gap is preventing these valid repairs from being generated.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":3220,"cache_read_input_tokens":48952,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":3220},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c37a3300-1904-44e6-bf34-65ba8b38fada","uuid":"ce4b638c-4afa-4d32-bc