oking verb detection to include `ugotuj` and similar variants, and implementing garbled token detection within multi-word candidates.\n\nI also need to add a position-0 score floor so candidates at the start of the file can't be easily beaten by body lines, fix how the pipe-separated metadata header interacts with the direct-successor bonus, and handle the case where the title is completely absent. Looking back at the Ogórkowa Zupa example, the metadata line with pipes should already be caught by the metadata detection logic, but I'll verify that's working correctly. Looking at what `looksLikeMetadata` actually checks for — it's scanning for patterns like \"SERVES\", \"PREP TIME\", and similar indicators, so the Polish equivalents in that line should trigger a match.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":5578,"cache_read_input_tokens":57963,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":5578},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c37a3300-1904-44e6-bf34-65ba8b38fada","uuid":"f6bac07e-c4f3-4c19-9c7a-12880c5c22aa"}
